WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.303
Previously on
"The Good Doctor"...

00:02.336 --> 00:06.207
I'm your neighbor. I'm in
the middle of "Uncharted,"
and I'm dead.

00:06.240 --> 00:07.341
Can I borrow
some triple A's?

00:07.375 --> 00:08.309
It's kind of silly,
isn't it?

00:08.342 --> 00:10.444
Our relationship --
that we're hiding it.

00:10.478 --> 00:12.580
We don't
have a relationship.

00:12.613 --> 00:14.148
We have sex.

00:14.182 --> 00:16.050
You're late.
No, the bus was late.

00:16.084 --> 00:17.351
I did nothing wrong.
The bus --

00:17.385 --> 00:18.719
Yeah.
This is gonna work out great.

00:18.752 --> 00:20.654
So you're treating him
like anybody else?

00:20.688 --> 00:22.090
You have any idea
how many patients

00:22.123 --> 00:23.291
he's scared the crap out of
today?

00:23.324 --> 00:24.258
So teach him.

00:24.292 --> 00:26.094
I'm teaching you both
that he doesn't belong.

00:26.127 --> 00:28.196
I hear
you got Shaun off scut

00:28.229 --> 00:29.230
and back into surgery.

00:29.263 --> 00:31.099
You figure you'll give him
a little authority,

00:31.132 --> 00:32.400
he'll screw something up.

00:32.433 --> 00:33.734
Andrews: Either way,
if he succeeds,

00:33.767 --> 00:35.169
I'm the guy
who just backed him.

00:35.203 --> 00:38.339
And if he fails,
I'm the president.

00:39.473 --> 00:42.110
[ Water dripping ]

00:42.143 --> 00:49.783
**

00:49.817 --> 00:52.553
[ Dripping continues ]

00:52.586 --> 01:02.630
**

01:02.663 --> 01:11.772
**

01:11.805 --> 01:14.608
[ Knock on door ]

01:14.642 --> 01:17.811
Hello.
I've looked everywhere.

01:17.845 --> 01:20.181
All right, I'm here now.
We'll...

01:20.214 --> 01:21.715
[ Sighs ]

01:21.749 --> 01:24.652
We'll just keep looking
until you find it.

01:24.685 --> 01:27.655
Why is the furniture
in the middle of the room?

01:27.688 --> 01:28.522
I know I packed it.

01:28.556 --> 01:31.659
I made a list.
"Star-tip screwdriver."

01:31.692 --> 01:34.128
Look, it's checked.

01:34.162 --> 01:35.529
It's checked.

01:35.563 --> 01:38.132
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:38.166 --> 01:45.806
**

01:45.839 --> 01:47.808
Maybe you -- you threw it out
with the newspapers

01:47.841 --> 01:49.177
you used to pack the dishes?

01:49.210 --> 01:50.578
I packed with bubble wrap.

01:50.611 --> 01:52.413
It's safer.
And you can see through it.

01:52.446 --> 01:53.381
Of course you did.

01:53.414 --> 01:56.317
Shaun, there's
a hardware store up the road.

01:56.350 --> 01:57.251
You can buy a new one.

01:57.285 --> 01:58.819
I don't want
a new screwdriver!

01:58.852 --> 02:00.288
I want my screwdriver!

02:00.321 --> 02:01.622
Stop it!

02:01.655 --> 02:03.824
**

02:05.593 --> 02:07.428
It's the middle of the --
I'm sorry.

02:07.461 --> 02:09.897
I just shouldn't have yelled.
J-Just...

02:09.930 --> 02:12.466
Let's just take a moment.
Sit down, please.

02:14.802 --> 02:17.238
Uh, you know what?

02:17.271 --> 02:21.309
We can use this for now,
okay?

02:21.342 --> 02:23.744
[ Stammers ]

02:23.777 --> 02:24.878
I can't stay here.

02:24.912 --> 02:25.879
Of course you can.

02:25.913 --> 02:27.648
It'll be fine.
I can't stay here.

02:27.681 --> 02:29.783
The...dishwasher
doesn't dry,

02:29.817 --> 02:31.752
the shower drain has
someone else's hair in it.

02:31.785 --> 02:34.855
And the crisper drawer
keeps coming off the track?

02:34.888 --> 02:37.758
I assume that's what
you were fixing.

02:39.427 --> 02:40.461
I forgot.

02:40.494 --> 02:41.795
Of course you forgot.

02:41.829 --> 02:42.863
It's understandable.

02:42.896 --> 02:44.898
You've been working
your ass off.

02:44.932 --> 02:47.635
You're exhausted.
You're under a lot of stress.

02:47.668 --> 02:48.936
There's a super
in the building.

02:48.969 --> 02:51.705
You can [Chuckles]
call him anytime.

02:51.739 --> 02:53.974
Just make a list of
the things you need repaired.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.609
Later, Shaun. Later.

02:55.643 --> 02:57.378
Later, Shaun!

02:59.313 --> 03:01.415
Go to bed.

03:12.693 --> 03:15.363
36 years old,
22 weeks pregnant.

03:15.396 --> 03:16.630
Ultrasound at 16 weeks

03:16.664 --> 03:18.499
revealed a tumor
on the fetus' tailbone.

03:18.532 --> 03:20.301
Mom's got
antiphospholipid syndrome.

03:20.334 --> 03:21.369
Makes surgery high risk.

03:21.402 --> 03:22.703
Also makes pregnancy
high risk.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.972
She's had three miscarriages.

03:25.005 --> 03:26.807
We need to do
an ultrasound and MRI

03:26.840 --> 03:29.377
to measure
the tumor's growth rate.

03:29.410 --> 03:32.646
Late bus doesn't explain
why you're showing up tired

03:32.680 --> 03:34.315
after you just had
12 hours off.

03:34.348 --> 03:35.916
We're all tired.

03:35.949 --> 03:37.718
Our last shift was 36 hours.

03:37.751 --> 03:40.254
I'm not interested in debating
the shift schedule with you.

03:40.288 --> 03:41.489
But I am curious
why you always feel

03:41.522 --> 03:43.591
the need to defend him.

03:43.624 --> 03:45.859
Well, we're all
on the same team.

03:45.893 --> 03:46.927
Yes.

03:46.960 --> 03:49.029
But you're all quarterbacks.

03:49.062 --> 03:50.564
And when training camp
is over,

03:50.598 --> 03:52.466
there's only gonna be
one starter.

03:52.500 --> 03:56.737
**

03:56.770 --> 04:00.007
[ Ultrasound whooshing ]

04:00.040 --> 04:01.742
Jared: The crown-rump length
of the fetus

04:01.775 --> 04:04.545
is 21.5 centimeters.

04:04.578 --> 04:05.646
[ Mouse clicking ]

04:05.679 --> 04:08.282
The diameter of the tumor
is...

04:08.316 --> 04:11.319
[ Mouse clicking ]

04:11.352 --> 04:13.387
...10.6 centimeters.

04:13.421 --> 04:15.723
Half the size
of the fetus.

04:15.756 --> 04:16.924
The tumor's grown.

04:16.957 --> 04:20.861
It's not cancer, but it is
monopolizing the blood supply,

04:20.894 --> 04:22.930
which is weakening
the fetus' heart.

04:22.963 --> 04:25.866
I'm sorry, but there's
no chance it would survive

04:25.899 --> 04:27.835
long enough to be viable.

04:27.868 --> 04:30.471
The safest course
is to terminate the pregnancy.

04:34.041 --> 04:36.544
If we were interested
in the "safest course,"

04:36.577 --> 04:38.846
we wouldn't be
on our third "second opinion."

04:38.879 --> 04:40.348
Please, Dr. Melendez,

04:40.381 --> 04:42.049
we want
whatever will save our baby.

04:42.082 --> 04:44.084
Dr. Wright told us
you've done fetal surgery

04:44.117 --> 04:45.886
to remove
this type of tumor before.

04:45.919 --> 04:47.888
And without the tumor,
our baby would be healthy.

04:49.590 --> 04:51.592
Your
antiphospholipid syndrome

04:51.625 --> 04:54.027
makes a long surgery
extremely dangerous.

04:54.061 --> 04:55.663
There's a high chance
for blood clots,

04:55.696 --> 04:57.598
which could have
fatal consequences for you.

04:57.631 --> 04:58.966
We're willing
to take that risk.

04:58.999 --> 05:00.834
Saving the fetus
doesn't do any good

05:00.868 --> 05:02.370
if the mother
dies in the process.

05:02.403 --> 05:04.638
I've had three miscarriages.

05:04.672 --> 05:07.007
If I have to go through that
again, I might as well be dead.

05:07.040 --> 05:08.842
Barb.
It's true.

05:08.876 --> 05:10.944
No, it's not.

05:10.978 --> 05:13.347
You're the strongest woman
I've ever met.

05:13.381 --> 05:14.448
We'll get through this.

05:14.482 --> 05:16.717
We will. And --
And then we'll try again.

05:16.750 --> 05:19.052
We could manage
clotting risk pre-operatively

05:19.086 --> 05:21.589
with an infusion
of unfractionated heparin.

05:21.622 --> 05:25.559
**

05:25.593 --> 05:28.496
[ Sighs ]

05:28.529 --> 05:30.931
Never contradict me
in front of a patient again.

05:30.964 --> 05:32.500
I didn't.

05:32.533 --> 05:34.535
I agree with your assessment
of the risks.

05:34.568 --> 05:36.036
I suggested a way
we could mitigate them.

05:36.069 --> 05:37.605
Not in front
of the patient.

05:37.638 --> 05:39.507
We're not in front
of the patient now.

05:39.540 --> 05:43.076
I was just reading
about a new technique

05:43.110 --> 05:46.046
for transesophageal
echocardiography monitoring.

05:46.079 --> 05:47.681
If there's a cardiac issue,

05:47.715 --> 05:49.483
it would give us
an early warning.

05:49.517 --> 05:53.487
**

05:53.521 --> 05:55.623
Let's get her prepped.
ASAP.

05:55.656 --> 05:59.627
**

05:59.660 --> 06:02.696
-- Captions by VITAC --

06:02.730 --> 06:07.601
**

06:10.471 --> 06:12.039
I want J.L. on anesthesia.

06:12.072 --> 06:13.774
And let
the neo-natal nursing supervisor

06:13.807 --> 06:15.075
know that I want to do
a full run-through.

06:15.108 --> 06:18.078
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
Damn it.

06:18.111 --> 06:19.813
Yes?

06:19.847 --> 06:22.483
Well, we're a little busy
up here, too.

06:22.516 --> 06:24.985
All right.
I'll send someone.

06:25.018 --> 06:26.854
Andrews is covering
for Lim in the ER.

06:26.887 --> 06:28.456
He has a patient
who needs a boil lanced.

06:28.489 --> 06:30.624
A plastic surgeon
can't lance a boil?

06:30.658 --> 06:32.826
Plastic surgeons can.
Chief surgeons don't.

06:32.860 --> 06:34.562
You and Murphy.

06:34.595 --> 06:36.464
What?

06:36.497 --> 06:37.831
It was our ideas
that convinced you

06:37.865 --> 06:38.932
to do the fetal surgery,

06:38.966 --> 06:41.935
and now you're punishing us
with Andrews' scut work?

06:41.969 --> 06:43.737
You're
not getting punished.

06:43.771 --> 06:44.738
He is.

06:44.772 --> 06:46.674
For being late.
Again.

06:46.707 --> 06:48.742
But I don't trust him alone
with a patient.

06:48.776 --> 06:50.077
And since you like
to defend him

06:50.110 --> 06:53.146
and seem to know how
to communicate with him...

06:53.180 --> 06:54.482
Hurry back.

06:54.515 --> 07:00.788
**

07:00.821 --> 07:01.855
Olivia Hartman?

07:01.889 --> 07:02.856
Yes, ma'am.

07:02.890 --> 07:04.825
I mean Doctor.

07:04.858 --> 07:06.760
You're 18?

07:06.794 --> 07:07.761
Yes, ma'am.

07:07.795 --> 07:08.762
Where's the boil?

07:08.796 --> 07:11.632
It's, um --
It's down there.

07:11.665 --> 07:12.833
Down where?

07:12.866 --> 07:15.836
Shaun.
It's, um, on her labia.

07:15.869 --> 07:18.138
Hmm.
Is it painful?

07:18.171 --> 07:20.207
Like I used a bowling ball
for a tampon.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.943
Okay. Boils shouldn't hurt
that much.

07:22.976 --> 07:24.712
Okay if we take a look?

07:24.745 --> 07:25.879
[ Breathes sharply ]

07:25.913 --> 07:26.980
Okay.

07:27.014 --> 07:28.782
If you just scoot down,

07:28.816 --> 07:30.651
put your feet
in the stirrups...

07:30.684 --> 07:33.521
**

07:33.554 --> 07:34.988
Great.

07:36.724 --> 07:39.092
The swelling
is fairly localized.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.929
Extreme pain that's out of
proportion to the visible injury

07:41.962 --> 07:44.197
could mean you have necrotizing
flesh-eating bacteria.

07:44.231 --> 07:45.232
What?!

07:45.265 --> 07:47.568
**

07:47.601 --> 07:50.270
I'm gonna use the heparin
pre-operatively

07:50.303 --> 07:51.872
and a T.E.E. monitor.

07:51.905 --> 07:53.106
Still not enough.

07:53.140 --> 07:54.942
The risk of a heart attack
or stroke --

07:54.975 --> 07:56.176
Was thoroughly explained.

07:56.209 --> 07:57.911
The patient
still wants the surgery.

07:57.945 --> 08:00.514
She wants it?
Or you want it?

08:02.883 --> 08:07.688
Yes, saving a fetus' life
would be good news for me.

08:07.721 --> 08:10.090
Any other questions?

08:10.123 --> 08:11.792
Or insults?

08:11.825 --> 08:13.727
Relax.
I'm not insulting you.

08:13.761 --> 08:15.963
Of course you want
to do the surgery.

08:15.996 --> 08:17.197
But you do
surgeries like this,

08:17.230 --> 08:18.866
some patients
are going to die.

08:18.899 --> 08:20.968
And then our department's
success rate goes down,

08:21.001 --> 08:21.902
and then our funding
goes down,

08:21.935 --> 08:24.171
and then you can't do
surgeries like this.

08:24.204 --> 08:26.807
So if your judgment
is clouded in any way, just --

08:26.840 --> 08:27.875
It's not.

08:29.810 --> 08:31.111
Okay.

08:37.618 --> 08:39.319
Aah!

08:39.352 --> 08:41.154
I'm sorry.
I know this hurts,

08:41.188 --> 08:43.123
but I really do need
to insert a speculum

08:43.156 --> 08:44.858
for this part
of the exam.

08:44.892 --> 08:46.560
If I really have
what he says,

08:46.594 --> 08:47.861
does that mean you have
to cut off my --

08:47.895 --> 08:50.798
No. No, as I said,
the abscess

08:50.831 --> 08:52.099
is most likely the result

08:52.132 --> 08:54.267
of an untreated
chlamydia infection.

08:54.301 --> 08:55.603
[ Echoing ]
We'll drain the abscess,

08:55.636 --> 08:56.837
give you antibiotics.

08:56.870 --> 08:59.006
[ Normal voice ]
You'll be fine.

08:59.039 --> 09:00.608
Ow!

09:00.641 --> 09:02.275
I'm -- I'm sorry.

09:02.309 --> 09:04.044
The inflamed Bartholin gland

09:04.077 --> 09:06.046
is causing
the ischiocavernosus muscle

09:06.079 --> 09:07.881
to spasm
and pinch the labial nerve.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.850
You need to start
with a more upward angle.

09:09.883 --> 09:11.084
Can I try?

09:11.118 --> 09:12.786
I think it's better
if I do this.

09:14.788 --> 09:16.323
Ow!

09:16.356 --> 09:18.759
[ Sighs ]

09:18.792 --> 09:20.761
Yeah, okay. Fine.

09:26.800 --> 09:29.269
Can we, uh, call your parents?
Let them know --

09:29.302 --> 09:30.804
No.

09:30.838 --> 09:33.006
I'm 18.
I'm an adult.

09:33.040 --> 09:34.875
Even adults need
emotional support.

09:34.908 --> 09:36.910
Someone to drive them home
after surgery.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.646
Uh, I'm gonna take
a taxi.

09:38.679 --> 09:39.980
I have money.

09:40.013 --> 09:41.649
There's nothing
to be embarrassed about.

09:41.682 --> 09:45.919
25% of college students contract
an STD before graduation.

09:45.953 --> 09:47.821
I'm not embarrassed.

09:47.855 --> 09:49.657
And I know all about STDs.

09:49.690 --> 09:51.725
I get tested
every 30 days.

09:51.759 --> 09:56.096
There's no necrosis
on the vaginal wall or cervix.

09:56.129 --> 09:57.765
You got it in already?

09:57.798 --> 10:00.901
Yes. It's definitely not
flesh-eating bacteria.

10:00.934 --> 10:02.402
I was wrong.
Thank God.

10:02.435 --> 10:05.205
You do need surgery to drain
the Bartholin gland abscess.

10:05.238 --> 10:07.875
Why do you get an STD test
every 30 days?

10:07.908 --> 10:10.644
I have to. For work.

10:12.379 --> 10:14.081
I do porn.

10:16.116 --> 10:18.652
The umbilical is 19 inches,

10:18.686 --> 10:21.689
which will allow us to remove
the fetus via Caesarean

10:21.722 --> 10:25.192
and rest it in its mother's lap
while I excise the tumor.

10:25.225 --> 10:26.794
Now, the hart part

10:26.827 --> 10:29.697
will be reinserting
the fetus afterwards.

10:29.730 --> 10:32.365
We can't overstretch
the uterine wall,

10:32.399 --> 10:35.235
and we must be certain that
every suture is tight enough

10:35.268 --> 10:40.307
to handle four more months
of kicks and thrown elbows.

10:40.340 --> 10:41.341
Do you have a minute?

10:41.374 --> 10:43.343
Can it wait?

10:43.376 --> 10:44.678
No.

10:44.712 --> 10:53.987
**

10:54.021 --> 10:55.923
I don't want to do it.

10:58.258 --> 10:59.760
Have you talked
to your wife?

10:59.793 --> 11:02.730
Yes, but she's
not thinking rationally.

11:02.763 --> 11:05.032
You heard her say she'd
rather die than lose this baby.

11:05.065 --> 11:07.267
I'm sorry, but husbands
don't have veto power

11:07.300 --> 11:08.936
over their wife's
medical decisions.

11:08.969 --> 11:11.471
**

11:11.504 --> 11:13.974
A husband can't stop you
from operating on his wife.

11:14.007 --> 11:17.044
But a father can stop you
from operating on his child.

11:17.077 --> 11:22.816
**

11:27.487 --> 11:29.056
**

11:29.089 --> 11:31.992
[ Chuckles ]
What kind of porn?

11:32.025 --> 11:33.994
[ Scoffs ]
I'm sorry.

11:34.027 --> 11:36.196
I was too busy doing
all the labs and imaging

11:36.229 --> 11:37.230
she needed for surgery.

11:37.264 --> 11:39.066
I forgot to ask
for her résumé.

11:39.099 --> 11:40.968
I just mean,
is she an actual actress,

11:41.001 --> 11:42.469
like in stuff with a story,
or --

11:42.502 --> 11:44.371
Do they even make porn
with stories anymore?

11:44.404 --> 11:47.207
Sometimes.

11:47.240 --> 11:49.376
You watch porn?

11:49.409 --> 11:51.011
Why wouldn't he?

11:51.044 --> 11:52.412
-I don't know. He just seems --
-He's a guy.

11:52.445 --> 11:54.247
All guys watch porn.

11:54.281 --> 11:55.816
You finished
with Andrews' patient?

11:55.849 --> 11:57.084
No.
It wasn't a boil.

11:57.117 --> 11:58.986
It's a large
Bartholin gland abscess

11:59.019 --> 12:00.320
that's pressing
on her pudendal nerve.

12:00.353 --> 12:02.489
Which apparently
does interest a chief surgeon.

12:02.522 --> 12:04.191
We're gonna assist Andrews
when he drains it

12:04.224 --> 12:05.025
first thing
in the morning.

12:05.058 --> 12:07.227
We just thought
we'd check with you.

12:07.260 --> 12:09.129
Go home.
And sleep.

12:09.162 --> 12:11.464
Not play video games or
whatever it is keeping you up.

12:11.498 --> 12:12.933
I don't think
it's video games.

12:12.966 --> 12:14.501
You can head out, too.
It's been a long day.

12:14.534 --> 12:16.837
But what about --
Fetal surgery's
been put on hold.

12:16.870 --> 12:18.471
What? Why?

12:18.505 --> 12:19.940
Go home.

12:19.973 --> 12:25.078
**

12:25.112 --> 12:27.280
Once the fetus
is removed from the uterus,

12:27.314 --> 12:28.982
one could argue
that it becomes a child.

12:29.016 --> 12:30.851
That's ridiculous.

12:30.884 --> 12:32.385
There are
numerous legal precedents --

12:32.419 --> 12:34.287
That guarantee
the mother's right to choose.

12:34.321 --> 12:35.989
It's her body.
It's her control.

12:36.023 --> 12:38.191
I'm completely comfortable
going ahead with this surgery.

12:38.225 --> 12:39.092
As am I.

12:39.126 --> 12:40.393
I never was,
and I certainly am not now.

12:40.427 --> 12:42.863
Jessica: I'm sorry. Until we're
certain there is no liability

12:42.896 --> 12:44.865
connected to parental consent,
neither am I.

12:44.898 --> 12:48.201
Well, the one thing
I think we can all agree on

12:48.235 --> 12:51.004
is that the mother
has the power to do nothing.

12:51.038 --> 12:53.073
And if she doesn't terminate

12:53.106 --> 12:55.175
or have the surgery
to remove the tumor...

12:55.208 --> 12:56.844
A fetus with a massive tumor

12:56.877 --> 12:59.246
will die
inside a patient with APS.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.048
Then the mother would die, too,
right?

13:01.081 --> 13:03.416
So we do nothing,
and they both die.

13:03.450 --> 13:05.418
Or we can do something

13:05.452 --> 13:08.588
that's legally
and ethically complicated,

13:08.621 --> 13:10.157
and maybe they both live.

13:10.190 --> 13:19.900
**

13:19.933 --> 13:21.234
[ Knocking ]

13:24.938 --> 13:26.239
The board
has approved the surgery.

13:26.273 --> 13:27.574
[ Breathes deeply ]

13:27.607 --> 13:29.176
Thank you.

13:29.209 --> 13:32.045
Barb, please --
Mark, stop.

13:32.079 --> 13:35.315
**

13:35.348 --> 13:37.050
If you loved me...

13:37.084 --> 13:37.851
No.

13:37.885 --> 13:40.120
No, do not say that.
No, it's true.

13:40.153 --> 13:42.189
If you really loved me --

13:42.222 --> 13:44.257
I'm trying to protect you
because I love you.

13:44.291 --> 13:47.427
I don't need
your protection.

13:49.629 --> 13:52.265
I need your support.

13:52.299 --> 13:54.968
We'll start prepping you
first thing in the morning.

13:55.002 --> 13:57.070
Try and get some sleep.

13:57.104 --> 13:58.972
Thank you.

13:59.006 --> 14:09.049
**

14:09.082 --> 14:11.151
**

14:11.184 --> 14:13.120
I still can't believe it.

14:16.223 --> 14:19.459
That 18-year-old
college students do porn?

14:19.492 --> 14:21.394
She's just not the type.

14:21.428 --> 14:22.529
How do you know
what "type" she is?

14:22.562 --> 14:23.463
You just met her.

14:23.496 --> 14:26.566
Did one medical history
and pelvic exam.

14:28.401 --> 14:30.670
What?

14:30.703 --> 14:31.939
Nothing.

14:31.972 --> 14:33.373
No, go ahead.

14:33.406 --> 14:35.075
Tell me all the reasons
why I'm wrong.

14:38.145 --> 14:41.314
I volunteered at a shelter
for runaway teens

14:41.348 --> 14:42.983
when I was at high school.

14:43.016 --> 14:45.085
Got to know
a lot of sex workers.

14:45.118 --> 14:46.453
They're not all the same,

14:46.486 --> 14:52.659
but they do have
the same...

14:52.692 --> 14:55.028
armor.

14:56.063 --> 14:57.998
I don't believe it.

14:58.031 --> 14:59.933
You think I'm lying?
No.

14:59.967 --> 15:02.069
No, I think
you just opened up to me,

15:02.102 --> 15:04.504
actually shared
something personal.

15:04.537 --> 15:06.606
[ Laughing ] It was
high-school community service.

15:06.639 --> 15:07.941
It's not a big deal.

15:07.975 --> 15:09.176
Oh, no, it's a big deal.

15:09.209 --> 15:10.610
This is huge.
Mm?

15:10.643 --> 15:12.579
I am peeling the onion.
Shut up.

15:12.612 --> 15:14.314
Actually, it's more like
hacking through a coconut

15:14.347 --> 15:15.415
with a dull machete, but --

15:15.448 --> 15:16.516
"Dull" is right.

15:16.549 --> 15:18.685
[ Chuckles ]
Very dull.

15:18.718 --> 15:21.288
It feels good, doesn't it?

15:21.321 --> 15:22.990
You should do it
more often.

15:23.023 --> 15:29.296
How about you stop worrying
about what I won't do

15:29.329 --> 15:31.464
and just enjoy
what I will?

15:31.498 --> 15:39.439
**

15:39.472 --> 15:43.576
Do you think
she's of sound mind?

15:43.610 --> 15:46.579
You really want to talk
about work right now?

15:46.613 --> 15:48.715
She's basically threatening
to commit suicide.

15:48.748 --> 15:50.717
She's not suicidal.

15:50.750 --> 15:53.586
She's -- She's just desperate
to have a child.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.055
This is
probably her last chance.

15:55.088 --> 15:56.990
She could adopt.

15:57.024 --> 15:59.659
It's not the same.
Really?

15:59.692 --> 16:01.328
You don't think
there's a difference?

16:01.361 --> 16:02.629
No, I don't.

16:02.662 --> 16:05.565
Carrying a fetus in your body
for nine months.

16:05.598 --> 16:08.235
You don't think that creates
a unique relationship?

16:08.268 --> 16:10.503
I think every relationship
is unique.

16:10.537 --> 16:12.572
Yeah, of course.

16:12.605 --> 16:14.041
What are you saying?

16:14.074 --> 16:16.376
I just think it's selfish.

16:16.409 --> 16:18.011
I mean, for her
to go through so much,

16:18.045 --> 16:20.180
to put your husband
through so much,

16:20.213 --> 16:21.748
just so you can have
a certain experience

16:21.781 --> 16:24.251
when there are other ways.

16:24.284 --> 16:26.119
Yeah, okay.

16:26.153 --> 16:28.755
But...you want children,
though, right?

16:28.788 --> 16:30.357
We've talked
about this before.

16:30.390 --> 16:32.425
Yes, I-I want children.

16:32.459 --> 16:33.793
But our children.

16:33.826 --> 16:35.395
Like,
from you getting pregnant.

16:35.428 --> 16:37.197
Yes.

16:38.698 --> 16:40.600
But what
if that doesn't happen?

16:40.633 --> 16:43.436
What if I couldn't
get pregnant

16:43.470 --> 16:46.506
or if I decided
that I didn't want to?

16:46.539 --> 16:48.341
That I wanted
to adopt instead?

16:48.375 --> 16:50.777
Is there something
you're not telling me?

16:50.810 --> 16:52.445
Actually, there is.

16:53.680 --> 16:55.348
When we're in meetings
together,

16:55.382 --> 16:57.317
don't ever call my ideas
"ridiculous."

16:57.350 --> 16:58.751
Come on,
I'm being serious.

16:58.785 --> 17:00.587
So am I.

17:02.522 --> 17:04.057
Okay.

17:04.091 --> 17:05.192
You're right.
I'm sorry.

17:05.225 --> 17:06.259
It won't happen again.

17:06.293 --> 17:16.269
**

17:16.303 --> 17:26.279
**

17:26.313 --> 17:28.315
**

17:29.649 --> 17:30.750
Steve:
Geez, you scared me.

17:30.783 --> 17:32.685
What're you reading?
Nothing.

17:32.719 --> 17:34.287
Can I read it?
No.

17:34.321 --> 17:36.189
Why?
Because.

17:36.223 --> 17:37.190
Why?

17:37.224 --> 17:38.825
Because.

17:38.858 --> 17:42.229
Why?

17:42.262 --> 17:45.232
Because there's nothing
to read.

17:45.265 --> 17:46.733
Just pictures.

17:46.766 --> 17:48.101
Where'd you get this?

17:48.135 --> 17:49.569
Colleen Myers.

17:49.602 --> 17:51.304
Her dad has so many
in his closet,

17:51.338 --> 17:53.440
he doesn't even notice
when she takes a few.

17:53.473 --> 17:55.375
She's pretty.

17:55.408 --> 17:56.843
She sure is.

17:56.876 --> 17:58.278
[ Door opens ]

17:58.311 --> 17:59.846
It's bedtime.

17:59.879 --> 18:01.181
That means lights out.

18:01.214 --> 18:04.184
**

18:04.217 --> 18:05.452
[ Door closes ]

18:05.485 --> 18:06.486
[ Sighs ]

18:14.594 --> 18:18.465
**

18:18.498 --> 18:20.133
I missed my stop.

18:20.167 --> 18:22.402
I missed my stop!

18:22.435 --> 18:24.204
Lynwood Place!
[ Brakes hiss ]

18:24.237 --> 18:26.206
I need to get off
at Lynwood Place.

18:26.239 --> 18:27.707
Well, then you should've
been paying attention

18:27.740 --> 18:30.710
when I stopped
at Lynwood Place.

18:30.743 --> 18:32.545
Next stop's gonna be
even further away,

18:32.579 --> 18:34.347
so if I were you...

18:34.381 --> 18:36.483
[ Engine idling ]

18:36.516 --> 18:46.493
**

18:46.526 --> 18:56.503
**

18:56.536 --> 19:06.579
**

19:10.617 --> 19:16.823
**

19:16.856 --> 19:19.392
[ Vehicle approaching ]

19:19.426 --> 19:21.794
[ Brakes squeal ]

19:21.828 --> 19:23.296
Lea: Shaun?

19:23.330 --> 19:25.332
Are you okay?

19:25.365 --> 19:26.599
Yes.

19:26.633 --> 19:28.535
Are you waiting
for someone?

19:28.568 --> 19:30.403
No.

19:30.437 --> 19:33.773
**

19:33.806 --> 19:36.576
Lea: I'm horrible
at directions, too.

19:36.609 --> 19:37.977
Every time
I exit a BART station,

19:38.010 --> 19:39.846
I walk like three blocks

19:39.879 --> 19:43.616
before I realize
I'm going the wrong direction.

19:43.650 --> 19:46.419
You're lucky
I actually made it to the gym.

19:46.453 --> 19:48.455
I like to go
when it's not crowded,

19:48.488 --> 19:50.923
but it's so hard
to motivate after work.

19:50.957 --> 19:52.325
Half the time
I end up not --

19:52.359 --> 19:55.295
You stink.
[ Chuckles ]

19:55.328 --> 19:56.829
I know.
I'm disgusting.

19:56.863 --> 19:59.232
But I can't shower there.

19:59.266 --> 20:01.801
I'm terrified
of foot fungus.

20:01.834 --> 20:04.237
Hey, you know, as long as we're
tossing out truth grenades,

20:04.271 --> 20:05.838
you suck
at being a neighbor.

20:05.872 --> 20:07.940
First, you take back
your batteries,

20:07.974 --> 20:09.942
and then you wake me up
in the middle of the night

20:09.976 --> 20:12.512
stomping around
and banging on pipes.

20:12.545 --> 20:13.746
What the hell's up
with that?

20:13.780 --> 20:15.715
My sink drips.

20:15.748 --> 20:17.517
I couldn't sleep,
so I tried to fix it.
[ Siren wailing ]

20:17.550 --> 20:19.319
Then I couldn't find
my screwdriver,

20:19.352 --> 20:20.653
which made me anxious.

20:20.687 --> 20:22.455
You kept me up
because you were anxious

20:22.489 --> 20:23.823
about a screwdriver?

20:23.856 --> 20:26.493
Yes.
I was very anxious.

20:26.526 --> 20:29.662
You're funny.

20:29.696 --> 20:32.465
I stink.
You're anxious.

20:32.499 --> 20:35.668
You always say
exactly what's on your mind.

20:35.702 --> 20:38.305
It's the total opposite
of most guys.

20:38.338 --> 20:41.308
It's nice.

20:41.341 --> 20:44.511
**

20:50.483 --> 20:52.619
Good night.

20:52.652 --> 20:55.288
And don't go fixing
any faucets tonight.

20:55.322 --> 20:56.423
That's Armen's job.

20:56.456 --> 20:58.024
[ Lock disengages, door opens ]

20:59.992 --> 21:02.895
[ Door closes ]

21:15.908 --> 21:19.078
This is a list of repairs
I need for my apartment.

21:19.111 --> 21:20.913
Number 33.

21:20.947 --> 21:22.815
What the hell
is your problem?

21:22.849 --> 21:24.751
Sorry. Hello.

21:24.784 --> 21:27.520
My name is Shaun Murphy.
It's very nice to meet you.

21:27.554 --> 21:31.891
No, it's not nice
to meet me at 12:40 a.m.

21:31.924 --> 21:33.693
Yes.

21:33.726 --> 21:35.528
Dr. Glassman said
I can call you

21:35.562 --> 21:37.430
any time
I need something fixed.

21:37.464 --> 21:38.565
Who the hell
is Dr. Glassman?

21:38.598 --> 21:41.634
He's the president at San Jose
St. Bonaventure Hospital.

21:41.668 --> 21:43.069
I'm a surgical resident
there.

21:43.102 --> 21:46.339
Well, I don't care if you're
St. Bonaventure himself.

21:46.373 --> 21:49.909
Unless it's a fire or flood,
I only work 9:00 to 5:00.

21:49.942 --> 21:51.744
Mm, I'll...

21:51.778 --> 21:53.813
try and come back tomorrow
between those times.

21:53.846 --> 21:57.584
You already woke me up.
Just give me the damn list.

21:58.885 --> 22:01.020
[ Door slams ]

22:01.053 --> 22:02.789
Glassman:
It's my fault.

22:02.822 --> 22:06.092
I should've known you would
take what I said literally.

22:06.125 --> 22:07.760
It's okay.

22:07.794 --> 22:10.062
Actually,
you know what, Shaun?

22:10.096 --> 22:11.564
It's not my fault.

22:11.598 --> 22:13.900
It's your responsibility.
You're smart.

22:13.933 --> 22:15.935
You should be able
to use your common sense.

22:15.968 --> 22:17.504
When somebody says something,

22:17.537 --> 22:19.672
you should figure out
what they really mean.

22:19.706 --> 22:23.776
And when things don't go
exactly how you expected them,

22:23.810 --> 22:25.578
navigate that.

22:25.612 --> 22:30.583
**

22:30.617 --> 22:34.454
[ Sighs ] There's a thing called
a Personal Support Worker.

22:34.487 --> 22:35.922
Think of it like
a home health aide.

22:35.955 --> 22:37.056
No, thank you.

22:37.089 --> 22:38.591
I can take care of myself.

22:38.625 --> 22:40.593
Everybody needs
a little help now and then.

22:40.627 --> 22:43.095
I-I'm thinking of asking them
to give me one.

22:43.129 --> 22:45.097
I've lived by myself
a long time.

22:45.131 --> 22:47.467
In Casper, Wyoming.

22:47.500 --> 22:49.001
Everybody looked out for you
in Casper.

22:49.035 --> 22:50.737
Everybody looks out
for everybody in Casper.

22:50.770 --> 22:52.605
This is San Jose.
It's a big city.

22:52.639 --> 22:55.575
And residency is a whole lot
more demanding than medical --

22:55.608 --> 22:56.709
I don't need an aide.

22:56.743 --> 22:57.744
We're just talking, Shaun.

22:57.777 --> 22:59.879
I don't need an aide!
Okay, okay.

22:59.912 --> 23:02.549
Okay.
Okay.

23:02.582 --> 23:04.884
Okay.

23:04.917 --> 23:07.720
We'll table it
for some other time.

23:09.221 --> 23:12.492
Let's enjoy our breakfast,
okay?

23:12.525 --> 23:14.994
**

23:20.500 --> 23:22.902
Mr. Allen?

23:22.935 --> 23:25.004
I'm trying to convince her
to save herself.

23:25.037 --> 23:26.973
I don't want to roll the dice
with my wife's life.

23:27.006 --> 23:29.008
But she does.

23:29.041 --> 23:30.176
We're gonna start
prepping her now,

23:30.209 --> 23:33.112
and she goes into the O.R.
in a few hours.

23:33.145 --> 23:34.881
I understand
why she desperate.

23:34.914 --> 23:37.784
But not why you are.

23:37.817 --> 23:39.852
If she dies,
it's your fault.

23:39.886 --> 23:42.021
And what if she lives?

23:43.823 --> 23:45.792
You're gonna have a wife
and child who need you,

23:45.825 --> 23:48.628
and you keep driving her
out of your life.

23:48.661 --> 23:50.597
I'm not desperate.

23:50.630 --> 23:52.565
I'm confident.

23:52.599 --> 23:54.467
Which should make
you feel better.

24:03.576 --> 24:04.944
[ Monitor beeping ]

24:04.977 --> 24:06.679
Retraction.

24:06.713 --> 24:07.980
I'll make the incision,

24:08.014 --> 24:10.983
and then I want you
to insert the Word catheter.

24:11.017 --> 24:13.219
Good job on the pelvic exam,
Dr. Murphy.

24:13.252 --> 24:15.021
With all this swelling,
it couldn't have been easy.

24:15.054 --> 24:16.022
Thank you.

24:16.055 --> 24:17.256
How do you know who...

24:17.289 --> 24:18.958
Oh, I have my ways.

24:18.991 --> 24:19.959
Like Santa.

24:19.992 --> 24:21.494
I told him.
Hm.

24:21.528 --> 24:22.595
No presents for you.

24:22.629 --> 24:23.696
Insert the drain.

24:26.699 --> 24:27.834
But I'm curious.

24:27.867 --> 24:30.837
How could a guy who can't
even shake a co-worker's hand

24:30.870 --> 24:33.706
be comfortable
doing a pelvic exam?

24:33.740 --> 24:35.875
People squeeze too hard.
It hurts.

24:35.908 --> 24:39.712
Send this to the lab
for culture.

24:39.746 --> 24:42.248
So, I'm guessing
you're not that into hugs.

24:42.281 --> 24:44.784
I don't like
to be squeezed.

24:44.817 --> 24:46.786
Well, what if it's
somebody you like?

24:46.819 --> 24:48.254
Or somebody you love?

24:48.287 --> 24:50.189
Have you ever had
a girlfriend?

24:52.124 --> 24:54.827
I almost kissed a girl.
Once.

24:54.861 --> 24:55.995
Well, you know
what they say --

24:56.028 --> 24:58.765
If at first
you don't succeed...

24:58.798 --> 25:01.033
Are you trying to mock me
or encourage me?

25:01.067 --> 25:02.802
I'm trying to get to know you

25:02.835 --> 25:06.072
so I know when I should mock
and when I should encourage.

25:06.105 --> 25:09.041
When's the right time
to mock you?

25:13.613 --> 25:14.981
**

25:15.014 --> 25:16.983
Press harder
on that abscess.

25:17.016 --> 25:18.217
It should have drained
by now.

25:18.250 --> 25:20.019
Something's wrong.

25:20.052 --> 25:23.089
The gland's evacuated, but
the swelling's not going down.

25:23.122 --> 25:24.657
Heart rate and BP
are stable.

25:24.691 --> 25:28.194
Can I get a little more light,
please?

25:28.227 --> 25:29.962
Damn.
What is it?

25:29.996 --> 25:31.564
The swelling isn't going down

25:31.598 --> 25:33.733
because there's a mass
beneath the abscess.

25:33.766 --> 25:36.035
And it's not just pressing
on the pudendal nerve --

25:36.068 --> 25:37.169
It's totally engulfed it.

25:37.203 --> 25:38.638
That's bad.

25:38.671 --> 25:39.672
Very bad.

25:39.706 --> 25:42.241
**

25:47.146 --> 25:48.615
[ Door opens, knock on door ]

25:48.648 --> 25:52.284
-You're done already?
-[ Breathes deeply ]

25:52.318 --> 25:55.121
We were able
to drain the abscess.

25:55.154 --> 25:57.156
I already feel better.

25:57.189 --> 25:58.925
Shaun: That's only because
of the pain meds.

25:58.958 --> 26:00.593
The reason
the pain was so severe

26:00.627 --> 26:02.128
was because it wasn't
just an abscess.

26:02.161 --> 26:04.831
There's perineal myoma
underneath.

26:04.864 --> 26:06.633
What's that?

26:06.666 --> 26:09.035
A fibroid tumor.

26:09.068 --> 26:13.172
It's not cancerous, but it is
wrapped around the nerve.

26:13.205 --> 26:14.774
We need to remove the tumor,

26:14.807 --> 26:18.310
but to do that,
we will have to sever the nerve.

26:18.344 --> 26:22.214
You'll lose all feeling
in your genitals.

26:22.248 --> 26:24.083
I'm so sorry.

26:24.116 --> 26:27.019
I knew it.

26:29.822 --> 26:31.023
God's punishing me.

26:31.057 --> 26:32.759
No, absolutely not.

26:32.792 --> 26:33.926
This is
just a random growth --

26:33.960 --> 26:35.161
You're religious?

26:35.194 --> 26:36.696
Yes.

26:36.729 --> 26:39.899
Or at least I used to be.

26:41.400 --> 26:44.170
I haven't thought about God
in a really long time.

26:44.203 --> 26:47.039
But being in here...

26:47.073 --> 26:49.208
You sure you don't want us
to call your parents?

26:49.241 --> 26:54.080
No. I couldn't bear to see
the look on their faces.

26:54.113 --> 26:55.815
Especially my dad's.

26:55.848 --> 26:59.251
Well, that's what parents
are for.

26:59.285 --> 27:01.654
So you don't have
to do these things alone.

27:01.688 --> 27:05.357
Could you tell your father
you're a whore?

27:05.391 --> 27:08.227
You made a mistake.

27:08.260 --> 27:09.829
That is all.

27:09.862 --> 27:13.199
**

27:13.232 --> 27:15.768
[ Monitor beeping ]

27:15.802 --> 27:18.004
Patient vitals?
Stable.

27:18.037 --> 27:19.371
Fetus?
Stable.

27:19.405 --> 27:20.873
Okay.

27:20.907 --> 27:23.009
Is everybody ready?

27:23.042 --> 27:24.276
Knife.

27:32.719 --> 27:34.153
[ Suction hissing ]

27:36.856 --> 27:37.957
Retractor.

27:52.038 --> 27:53.940
Okay.

27:53.973 --> 27:55.742
Cutting into the uterus.

27:55.775 --> 27:58.210
**

27:58.244 --> 27:59.278
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

27:59.311 --> 28:00.279
[ Alarm beeping ]

28:00.312 --> 28:02.715
T.E.E. is showing
anterior wall hypokinesis.

28:02.749 --> 28:04.416
Systolic pressure 90.
Get me a Swan.

28:04.450 --> 28:05.818
I.V. function
is decreasing.

28:05.852 --> 28:06.886
She's having a heart attack.

28:06.919 --> 28:07.987
I need you
to close the incision.

28:08.020 --> 28:09.889
-On it. Needle driver.
-Get a fluoroscope in here!

28:09.922 --> 28:11.758
I'm gonna prep her
for a balloon pump.

28:11.791 --> 28:14.160
**

28:14.193 --> 28:17.096
Melendez: Barbara?

28:17.129 --> 28:19.298
There was a complication
during surgery.

28:19.331 --> 28:21.834
A blood clot blocked
an artery in your heart.

28:21.868 --> 28:23.970
We were able
to catch it in time.

28:24.003 --> 28:24.971
And my baby?

28:25.004 --> 28:27.373
The fetus is stable.

28:27.406 --> 28:30.843
The M.I. happened
before we opened the uterus.

28:30.877 --> 28:32.845
So, we're right back
where we started?

28:32.879 --> 28:35.247
You just had
a heart attack.

28:35.281 --> 28:36.315
I don't care.

28:36.348 --> 28:38.050
There is
no other option now.

28:38.084 --> 28:40.386
If we don't terminate
